# SSTracker agent workflow

## Before coding

- Read [`docs/vision/PRODUCT_SURFACE_REGISTRY.md`](../../docs/vision/PRODUCT_SURFACE_REGISTRY.md) — confirm **current tier**, `nav_visible`, `workflow_id`, and `layout_pattern` for every route you touch; do not add nav links for Tier 2/3 without owner registry update.
- Read [`docs/vision/PLATFORM_WORKFLOW_CANON.md`](../../docs/vision/PLATFORM_WORKFLOW_CANON.md) — gold path step ids + UX states for the route's `workflow_id`.
- Read [`docs/vision/PLATFORM_NAVIGATION_CANON.md`](../../docs/vision/PLATFORM_NAVIGATION_CANON.md) — field/desk breakpoints, Option D pin bar + AppMenuSheet, staff-admin bucket, skin separation before any shell / nav / layout work.
- Read [`docs/vision/PLATFORM_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`](../../docs/vision/PLATFORM_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md) + persona **foundation_doc** from registry — shell contract + layout pattern before pixels.
- Read **`ROADMAP.md`** — current sprint section only. Do not invent sprint numbers or component names from archived roadmaps.
- For any **Player UX / layout / pixel** work: read [`docs/vision/PLAYER_OS_INSTRUMENT_TAXONOMY.md`](../../docs/vision/PLAYER_OS_INSTRUMENT_TAXONOMY.md) and [`docs/vision/AGENT_PLAYER_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/vision/AGENT_PLAYER_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md) **before** coding — classify instrument(s) and cohesion scope (Frame | Inner | Both).
- For any **Coach UX / layout / pixel** work: read [`docs/vision/COACH_OS_FOUNDATION.md`](../../docs/vision/COACH_OS_FOUNDATION.md) and [`docs/vision/AGENT_COACH_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/vision/AGENT_COACH_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md) — **reject Trinity HUD overlay on Tier 1** (`/coach`, `/coach/forge`).
- For any **Parent UX / layout / pixel** work: read [`docs/vision/PARENT_OS_FOUNDATION.md`](../../docs/vision/PARENT_OS_FOUNDATION.md) and [`docs/vision/AGENT_PARENT_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/vision/AGENT_PARENT_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md) — 390px first.
- For any **UX / pixel / copy** work: read [`docs/vision/PLATFORM_BUILD_MANDATES.md`](../../docs/vision/PLATFORM_BUILD_MANDATES.md), then [`docs/vision/PLATFORM_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`](../../docs/vision/PLATFORM_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md), then [`docs/vision/PLATFORM_EXPERIENCE_RUBRIC.md`](../../docs/vision/PLATFORM_EXPERIENCE_RUBRIC.md), then the persona vision doc from [`docs/PERSONA_ECOSYSTEM.md`](../../docs/PERSONA_ECOSYSTEM.md).
- Check persona **foundation_doc** from registry: [`PLAYER_OS_FOUNDATION.md`](../../docs/vision/PLAYER_OS_FOUNDATION.md) · [`COACH_OS_FOUNDATION.md`](../../docs/vision/COACH_OS_FOUNDATION.md) · [`PARENT_OS_FOUNDATION.md`](../../docs/vision/PARENT_OS_FOUNDATION.md).
- Check [`docs/PERSONA_ECOSYSTEM.md`](../../docs/PERSONA_ECOSYSTEM.md) for persona boundaries when UX intent matters.

## Scope discipline

- **One slice per session** — touch 5 or fewer files unless the sprint doc explicitly lists more.
- **Extend sprint test files** — add guards to `playerHudSprint*.test.ts`, `firestoreRulesSprint*.test.ts`, etc. Never delete prior sprint regression tests.
- **Do not create** duplicate roadmap files or `MASTER_BUILD_ROADMAP.md`. `ROADMAP.md` is canonical.
- **Player OS gate:** Epic 3.4+ / 4.1+ **may proceed** after ROADMAP marks **2.19 Done** (Player OS cinematic premium track). Tier B foundation 2.12–2.15 alone is insufficient.
- Premium sprints require **visual acceptance states** in sprint scope (not CSS string scans alone).

## Canonical player dashboard names

Use these names — **not** IdentityModule, TelemetryPanel, or BentoGrid:

- `IdentityBentoModule`
- `OperativeHub`
- `HudMetricsPanel`
- `ActiveBounties`
- `VanguardProtocolPanel`
- `HUDContainer`

## Known anti-patterns

- Do **not** refactor `teamsStore` for mission dedup — use `deduplicateById` in `ActiveBounties`.
- Do **not** add gamification chrome to Coach OS routes.
- Do **not** ship Trinity HUD overlay (`IntentHUD` fixed bottom panel) on Coach Tier 1 routes — Forge = full-page workbench per [`COACH_OS_FOUNDATION.md`](../../docs/vision/COACH_OS_FOUNDATION.md).
- Do **not** implement planned roles (`team_manager`, etc.) in JWT/route code unless a sprint explicitly says so.
- Do **not** wrap Tier A primitives (VanguardCard / SkillTreeArena / pdDataBloom / ProvingGrounds) in Tier B matte panels with multiple decorative borders.
- Do **not** introduce inner `overflow: auto` regions on Player OS routes (use native document scroll).
- Do **not** ship route-only UX without instrument type classification per [`PLAYER_OS_INSTRUMENT_TAXONOMY.md`](../../docs/vision/PLAYER_OS_INSTRUMENT_TAXONOMY.md).
- Do **not** apply Navigation tile chrome (Z3 lift tiles, nav accent frames) on Telemetry surfaces (`VanguardProtocolPanel`, Stats investigation bands).

## Mode split

- **Design** → Ask mode → vision docs under `docs/vision/`.
- **Build** → Agent mode → ROADMAP sprint ticket with explicit file list.

## Verify before done

**Per ROADMAP slice (mandatory loop — do not batch slices):**

1. `npm test -- <paths from ROADMAP sprint>`
2. **Before merge/deploy:** `npm run test:regression:acquisition && npm run build` (or `npm run audit:pre-deploy` for check + build). **Fail closed** — do not mark slice done if regression bundle regressed.
3. **After deploy:** `npm run smoke:dev` (network probes complement vitest guards).
4. `npm run build` (skip `npm run check` only if failures are pre-existing and unrelated to the slice; `audit:pre-deploy` runs check when used)
5. **Deploy to `sports-skill-tracker-dev`** — this Firebase project **is production / live-fire** for owner QA (not a throwaway sandbox). Default: hosting + rules + the sprint's `deploy:*` script(s).
6. **One git commit per slice** — commit immediately after deploy succeeds; never combine multiple ROADMAP rows (e.g. LAUNCH-rsvp + LAUNCH-tryouts-a) into one commit.

```bash
npm run test:regression:acquisition && npm run build
npm test -- <paths from ROADMAP sprint>
npm run build
# nav / shell canon slices:
npm test -- src/lib/platform/__tests__/platformNavigationCanon.test.ts \
  src/lib/platform/__tests__/parentNavWorkflow.guard.test.ts \
  src/lib/shell/__tests__/fieldMenuSheet.test.ts \
  src/lib/parent/__tests__/householdClearanceLoad.test.ts \
  src/lib/platform/__tests__/ownerQaWorkflowCoverage.test.ts \
  src/lib/platform/__tests__/productSurfaceRegistry.test.ts
# deploy (example tryouts slice):
npm run deploy:core
firebase deploy --only firestore:rules,hosting
git commit -m "<slice id>: <why>"
```

**Large Cloud Functions deploys:** use `npm run deploy:core` and `npm run deploy:rl` (not full `firebase deploy --only functions`) — see [`docs/FUNCTIONS_DEPLOY.md`](../../docs/FUNCTIONS_DEPLOY.md).

**Nav / shell / parent Tier-1 slices:** Any change to `MobilePinBar`, `AppMenuSheet`, `navPinCatalog`, or parent Tier-1 routes (`/parent/household`, `/parent/vpc`, `/parent/dashboard`) requires the owner Phase 4b retest matrix in PR summary — agents must **not** mark Phase 4b or GP-ACQ-01 complete. See [`docs/vision/AGENT_NAV_SLICE_TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/vision/AGENT_NAV_SLICE_TEMPLATE.md).
